{
  "stem": "11472.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When you saw the Germans come-- grabbing men for slave labor camp, because the boys knew if they were caught, they were destined for death.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Scared, frightened.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You used to shiver.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm still shaking when I think about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because when you saw Germans, you knew that a great catastrophe is going to happen any minute.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You didn't know what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, one day it was Passover time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was already in 1942, Passover time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Germans made a trap for all the young men in our area.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] What happened was, they said that all the boys over 13, up to the age of 50, have to come to Borschtov, and there they will have-- they have tables set up, and they will give them passports.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If they will be caught without those passports, they are going to be shot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So people started to look to-- to hire a peasant.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we had-- we had a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But our ghetto was not surrounded by barbed wire, since we all-- the Jews lived all in-- in-- surrounded in a circle like.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the Ukrainian police were watching us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When did people-- when were people forced to go or move to the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right away, as soon as the Germans came in, the surrounding villages, all the people came to our ghetto and they made a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in-- no, '41.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'41.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we-- '41.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my grandmother's sister, Leicha Wechsler, and her son Shermer Wechsler, and her son Luncher Wechsler came to my house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my grandmother had a very big house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So her other sister, Chencha Kimmelman and Mendel Kimmelman-- and their daughter, [NON-ENGLISH], Charna, and Schloime, their son, moved into them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And most of the people lived with other people.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
